**scetch business model based on following description: Customers: Enpal's primary stakeholders are its customers who purchase and use the solar panel systems. Customers benefit from reduced energy bills, lower carbon footprint, and the convenience of having a one-stop-shop for solar panel installation, financing, and maintenance. Financing partners: Enpal works with financing partners, such as banks and investors, to provide financing options to its customers. Financing partners benefit from a reliable source of income through the interest paid on loans, while also contributing to the adoption of renewable energy. Installation partners: Enpal works with installation partners, such as contractors and electricians, to install solar panel systems. Installation partners benefit from a steady flow of business, while also contributing to the growth of the renewable energy industry. Maintenance partners: Enpal works with maintenance partners, such as technicians and monitoring companies, to ensure the proper functioning of solar panel systems. Maintenance partners benefit from a steady flow of business, while also contributing to the growth of the renewable energy industry. Energy suppliers: Enpal sells excess energy generated by the solar panel systems back to the grid, making them a stakeholder in the business model. Energy suppliers benefit from a more diversified and renewable energy supply, helping to reduce their carbon footprint and ensure a reliable energy supply. Regulatory bodies: Regulatory bodies, such as governments and energy regulators, also play a role in Enpal's business model. They create policies and regulations that support the growth of renewable energy, which can benefit Enpal and its stakeholders.
